de.must.dataobj
Class Identifier

java.lang.Object
  de.must.dataobj.Identifier

public class Identifier
extends java.lang.Object

Abstract identifier of table entries - no matter what their primary key is. The preferred way of accessing records is a unique key with one numeric field. Anyhow, to support older database designs, there may be a need to identify records via multiple key fields, maybe including different field types. To avoid switches in many components, all primary key cases are wrapped in this identifier class. Thus, only one type of object has to be passed.

See Also:
IdentifyTemplate, DataObject
